.TH alignObject  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBalignObject\fR \-  Aligns objects (instances, modules, or blockages) vertically or horizontally in the floorplan. Use this command after selecting two or more objects in the design display area
.SH Syntax \fBalignObject\fR   [-help]  -side {right | left | center | top | bottom | middle}   [-referToFirst]  [-mix]
.P Aligns objects (instances, modules, or blockages) vertically or horizontally in the floorplan. Use this command after selecting two or more objects in the design display area. 
.SH Parameters   "\fB-help\fR" Outputs a brief description that includes the type and default information for each alignObject parameter. For a detailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use the man command:   man alignObject  "\fB-mix\fR" Considers all the selected objects together while aligning them.  Data_type: bool, optional  "\fB-referToFirst\fR" If you specify this option, the first selected object is the reference object.  Data_type: bool, optional  "\fB-side {right | left | center | top | bottom | middle}\fR" Specifies the vertical and horizontal alignment for the selected objects. Choose one of the following:
.RS  "*" 2 right: Specifies vertical right alignment.  "*" 2 left: Specifies vertical left alignment.  "*" 2 center: Specifies vertical center alignment.  "*" 2 top: Specifies horizontal top alignment.  "*" 2 bottom: Specifies horizontal bottom alignment.  "*" 2 middle: Specifies horizontal middle alignment.
.RE   Data_type: string, required 
.SH Example
.RS  "*" 2  The following command aligns the selected objects (Block) vertically to the left:  alignObject -side left  Before:                                                                  After:  (<Image> To view the image, refer to the Innovus Text Command Reference - Release 22.1 manual.)            (<Image> To view the image, refer to the Innovus Text Command Reference - Release 22.1 manual.)   "*" 2  The following command aligns the selected objects (Blockage、Module、Block) vertically to the left：  alignObject -side left -mix  Before:                                                 After：                           (<Image> To view the image, refer to the Innovus Text Command Reference - Release 22.1 manual.)             (<Image> To view the image, refer to the Innovus Text Command Reference - Release 22.1 manual.)   "*" 2 The following command aligns the selected objects (Block) vertically to the left：  alignObject -side left -referToFirst  Before：                                                                        After：  (<Image> To view the image, refer to the Innovus Text Command Reference - Release 22.1 manual.)             (<Image> To view the image, refer to the Innovus Text Command Reference - Release 22.1 manual.) 
.RE 
.SH Related Information
.RS  "*" 2 shiftOrigin  "*" 2 spaceObject  "*" 2 flipOrRotateObject  "*" 2 Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide
.RE
